(firstQuint)Prehabilitation for PAD Revascularization Patients.

 Patients undergoing elective revascularization for their peripheral artery disease will be randomized to a "prehabilitation" program prior to their surgery or to usual care.

 The prehabilitation program is self-directed program designed to improve health and quality of life prior to surgery.

 The program is currently offered to general surgery patients; this study will examine the feasibility and acceptability of such a program in a different patient population.

